      "meaning": "accustomed",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "v_wasureru",
      "surface": "忘れる",
      "reading": "わすれる",
      "meaning": "to forget",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "ichidan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "v_oboeru",
      "surface": "覚える",
      "reading": "おぼえる",
      "meaning": "to memorize / to remember",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "ichidan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "覚える = commit to memory (learning). Contrast with 思い出す = recall from memory."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_sameru",
      "surface": "覚める",
      "reading": "さめる",
      "meaning": "to wake up / to come to one's senses",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "ichidan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "Intransitive — the subject wakes up on their own. 目が覚める (eyes open / wake up). Contrast with 覚ます (transitive)."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_samasu",
      "surface": "覚ます",
      "reading": "さます",
      "meaning": "to wake someone up / to bring to one's senses",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "godan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "Transitive — someone wakes another person/thing. 目を覚ます (wake someone up). Contrast with 覚める (intransitive)."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_nareru",
      "surface": "慣れる",
      "reading": "なれる",
      "meaning": "to get used to / to grow accustomed to",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "ichidan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "Takes に: 日本の生活に慣れる (get used to life in Japan)."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_wasuremono",
      "surface": "忘れ物",
      "reading": "わすれもの",
      "meaning": "forgotten item / lost property",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "noun",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "忘 (N3.1) + 物 (N4.5). Common at train stations and schools."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_bounenkai",
      "surface": "忘年会",
      "reading": "ぼうねんかい",
      "meaning": "year-end party / end-of-year gathering",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "noun",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "忘 (N3.1) + 年 (N5.4) + 会 (N5.17). Lit. forget-year-gathering. A major social tradition in Japanese workplaces and friend groups."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_shuukan",
      "surface": "習慣",
      "reading": "しゅうかん",
      "meaning": "habit / custom",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "noun",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "習 (N4.32) + 慣 (N3.1). 生活習慣 = lifestyle habits."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_jikaku",
      "surface": "自覚",
      "reading": "じかく",
      "meaning": "self-awareness / consciousness",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "noun",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "自 (N4.11) + 覚 (N3.1). 自覚がある = to be self-aware."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_mezamashi",
      "surface": "目覚まし",
      "reading": "めざまし",
      "meaning": "alarm clock",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "noun",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "目 (N5.18) + 覚ます (N3.1). Lit. eye-opener. Short for 目覚まし時計."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_neniri",
      "surface": "念入り",
      "reading": "ねんいり",
      "meaning": "careful / thorough / meticulous",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "na-adjective",
      "verb_class": "na_adj",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.1",
      "notes": "念 (N3.1) + 入 (N5.5). 念入りに準備する = to prepare carefully."
    },
    {
      "id": "k_ren",
      "lesson": "N3.2",
      "type": "kanji",
      "surface": "連",
      "on": "れん",
      "kun": "つれる/つらなる",
      "reading": "つれる",
      "meaning": "connect / link / take along",
      "notes": "Kun: つれる (take along), つらなる (line up). On: れん in compounds like 連絡, 連休."
    },
    {
      "id": "k_tatsu",
      "lesson": "N3.2",
      "type": "kanji",
      "surface": "達",
      "on": "たつ",
      "kun": "",
      "reading": "たつ",
      "meaning": "reach / attain / plural suffix",
      "notes": "On: たつ in 上達, 達人. Also read たち/だち as a plural/group suffix: 友達, 私たち."
    },
    {
      "id": "k_chigau",
      "lesson": "N3.2",
      "type": "kanji",
      "surface": "違",
      "on": "い",
      "kun": "ちがう/ちがえる",
      "reading": "ちがう",
      "meaning": "differ / wrong / violate",
      "notes": "Kun: ちがう (be different/wrong), ちがえる (mistake). On: い in 違反 (violation)."
    },
    {
      "id": "k_karamu",
      "lesson": "N3.2",
      "type": "kanji",
      "surface": "絡",
      "on": "らく",
      "kun": "からむ/からまる",
      "reading": "からむ",
      "meaning": "entangle / get involved",
      "notes": "Kun: からむ (get tangled/involved). On: らく in 連絡 (contact)."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_chigau",
      "surface": "違う",
      "reading": "ちがう",
      "meaning": "to be different / to be wrong",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "godan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.2",
      "notes": "それは違う = that's wrong. 意見が違う = opinions differ. One of the most common verbs in daily conversation."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_chigai",
      "surface": "違い",
      "reading": "ちがい",
      "meaning": "difference",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "noun",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.2",
      "notes": "文化の違い = cultural difference. AとBの違い = the difference between A and B."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_machigaeru",
      "surface": "間違える",
      "reading": "まちがえる",
      "meaning": "to make a mistake / to mix up",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "ichidan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.2",
      "notes": "間 (N5.14) + 違 (N3.2). Transitive: 道を間違えた (took the wrong road). AをBと間違える = to mistake A for B."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_machigau",
      "surface": "間違う",
      "reading": "まちがう",
      "meaning": "to be wrong / to be mistaken",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "godan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.2",
      "notes": "間 (N5.14) + 違 (N3.2). Intransitive: 答えが間違っている (the answer is wrong). Often used in ている form to describe a state."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_machigai",
      "surface": "間違い",
      "reading": "まちがい",
      "meaning": "mistake / error",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "noun",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.2",
      "notes": "間 (N5.14) + 違 (N3.2). 間違いなく = without a doubt. 間違いがある = there is a mistake."
    },
    {
      "id": "v_tsureru",
      "surface": "連れる",
      "reading": "つれる",
      "meaning": "to take someone along / to bring someone",
      "type": "vocab",
      "gtype": "verb",
      "verb_class": "ichidan",
      "lesson_ids": "N3.2",
      "notes": "子どもを連れて行く = to take a child along. 連れて来る = to bring someone."
    },
    {
